SIMPLE: sea_devil
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sea devil
<hw>Sea" dev`il</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd>
<def>Any very large ray, especially any species of the genus
<gen>Manta</gen> or <gen>Cephaloptera</gen>, some of which become more
than twenty feet across and weigh several tons. See also <cref>Ox
ray</cref>, under <er>Ox</er>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Any large
cephalopod, as a large Octopus, or a giant squid
(<gen>Architeuthis</gen>). See <er>Devilfish</er>.</def> <sd>(c)</sd>
<def>The angler.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sea dog</ent>⟦br⟧
